  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Insert Interval\n\nInsert a new interval into sorted non-overlapping intervals and merge overlaps.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: intervals = [[1,3],[6,9]], newInterval = [2,5]\nOutput: [[1,5],[6,9]]\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: intervals = [[1,2],[3,5],[6,7],[8,10]], newInterval = [4,8]\nOutput: [[1,2],[3,10]]\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: intervals = [], newInterval = [4,8]\nOutput: [[4,8]]\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return the value described by the method signature.",
  "editorial": "Track the local choice that leaves the most room for future choices, or sort intervals so conflicts can be resolved with one pass.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def insert(self, intervals, newInterval):\n        out = []\n        start, end = newInterval\n        placed = False\n        for a, b in intervals:\n            if b < start: out.append([a, b])\n            elif end < a:\n                if not placed: out.append([start, end]); placed = True\n                out.append([a, b])\n            else:\n                start, end = min(start, a), max(end, b)\n        if not placed: out.append([start, end])\n        return out\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Sort first when relative order drives the decision.",
    "Keep the smallest state that proves future feasibility."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def insert(self, intervals, newInterval):\n        pass\n"
  },
